</head>
<body>
    <center>

      <header>
        <div style="display:flex;justify-content: space-between;">
          <h1 style="margin-left: 600px;">Energy Conservation Hub </h1>
          <h1 style="margin-top: 35;margin-right: 60px;" class="button">User: <%= name %></h1>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section style="background-color: lightgreen;margin-top: 1.5%;">
        <h2>Welcome</h2>
        <h4>Welcome to our energy conservation guide. Here, you'll find valuable tips to help you
          save energy and reduce your environmental impact.</h4>
        </section>
      <section>
      <br>
      <center>
          <div class="tips">
            <h2 style="margin-left: 290px;color: black;"><strong>Energy Saving Tips</strong></h2>
            <div class="tip">
              <h3>1. Use Energy-Efficient Appliances</h3>
              <p>Upgrade to appliances with the ENERGY STAR label to save electricity and
                reduce your utility bills.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tip">
              <h3>2. Turn Off Lights When Not in Use</h3>
              <p>Remember to turn off lights and electronics when leaving a room to conserve
                energy.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tip">
              <h3>3. Adjust Thermostat Settings</h3>
              <p>Set your thermostat to an energy-saving temperature when you're away or asleep
                to save on heating and cooling costs.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tip">
              <h3>4. Unplug Chargers and Devices</h3>
              <p>Unplug chargers and electronic devices when they're not in use to prevent energy
                wastage.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
        <div class="tip" style="background-color: aquamarine;width:750px;height:40px;margin-right: 90px;padding: 0.6%;border: 1px solid black;text-align:center;">
          <h3>
            In case you have any queries please contact the website <a href="/query">www.queries.org</a>
          </h3>
        </div>
      </center>

    </center>

